New Records: The Houston Rockets set a new record with their 127-100 victory over the San Antonio Spurs.
Key Match Events: Alperen Şengün delivered a solid performance with 16 points, five rebounds, four assists, two blocks and one steal in 24 minutes of action.
Jalen Green and Fred VanVleet also contributed significantly, each adding 21 points, with VanVleet also dishing out 10 assists.
Victor Wembanyama scored 15 points and grabbed six rebounds, while Julian Champagnie posted 13 points and three boards.
Post-Match Reflections: The Houston Rockets secured their fifth win of the season with a dominant 127-100 victory over the San Antonio Spurs.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Cleveland Cavaliers set a franchise record with a perfect 9-0 start, defeating the New Orleans Pelicans 131-122.
Others: Donovan Mitchell led the way with 29 points and 4 rebounds, while Jarrett Allen contributed a double-double with 16 points and 14 rebounds, and Evan Mobley added 15 points and 9 boards.
